# Zed Task for Launching Phoenix Elixir Server

Here's a Zed task configuration to launch a Phoenix Elixir server. You can add this to your `.zed/tasks.json` file:

```json
{
  "tasks": {
    "phoenix-server": {
      "command": "mix phx.server",
      "cwd": "${workspaceRoot}",
      "env": {
        "MIX_ENV": "dev"
      },
      "initializationTimeout": 5000,
      "problemMatcher": {
        "pattern": {
          "regexp": "^\\[error\\] (.*) in (.*) at line (\\d+)$",
          "file": 2,
          "line": 3,
          "message": 1
        }
      },
      "presentation": {
        "echo": true,
        "reveal": "always",
        "focus": false,
        "panel": "dedicated",
        "showReuseMessage": false,
        "clear": false
      },
      "group": "build",
      "label": "Run Phoenix Server"
    }
  }
}
```

## How to Use
1. Create a `.zed` directory in your Phoenix project root if it doesn't exist
2. Create or edit `tasks.json` in the `.zed` directory and paste the above configuration
3. Launch Zed editor and open your Phoenix project
4. Use the command palette (Cmd+Shift+P or Ctrl+Shift+P) and type "Run Task"
5. Select "Run Phoenix Server" from the menu

This task will start your Phoenix server with the `mix phx.server` command in development mode.
